cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the classification of human and robot based on micro-Doppler signatures obtained from radar sensors. This involves analyzing joint Range-Doppler maps and using machine learning techniques for classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of robots and radar sensors, which suggests the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). The use of machine learning techniques for classification suggests the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of a Deep Convolutional Neural Network (DCNN) suggests the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
